import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['US_Gross'] = pd.to_numeric(data['US_Gross'], errors='coerce')
    data['Worldwide_Gross'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Worldwide_Gross'], errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='US_Gross', y='Worldwide_Gross', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between US Gross and Worldwide Gross?', wrap=True)
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Production_Budget'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Production_Budget'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Production_Budget', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Production_Budget'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Production_Budget'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Production Budget?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
